messages.message:
Hi team, I just restarted my sandbox and I am seeing the following error on  `webapp` `model-service` and `api-server`

```TypeError: Descriptors cannot be created directly.
If this call came from a _pb2.py file, your generated code is out of date and must be regenerated with protoc >= 3.19.0.
If you cannot immediately regenerate your protos, some other possible workarounds are:
 1. Downgrade the protobuf package to 3.20.x or lower.
 2. Set PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python (but this will use pure-Python parsing and will be much slower).```
Looks like this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/74000) was merged to address this a few weeks back, I had just pulled from master so those changes are already in.

Seems like there could be a fix here (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C06FA6A23/p1755912403954589?thread_ts=1755741284.222769&cid=C06FA6A23)? I'm just not sure how to update `googleapis-common-protos`
Nevermind, I added a feature flag which seemed to be the root cause
